3
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:17,260
(Choi Soo Young)

4
00:00:17,719 --> 00:00:20,589
(Won Ji An, Nam Tae Hoon, Yang Hee Kyung)

5
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:23,359
(Kil Hae Yeon, Yu Soon Woong, Jeon Chae Eun, Shin Ju Hwan)

6
00:00:30,699 --> 00:00:33,969
(If You Wish Upon Me)

7
00:00:34,210 --> 00:00:37,379
(I want to see the ocean for the last time.)

8
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:39,478
(Dutch ambulance driver Kees Veldboer...)

9
00:00:39,479 --> 00:00:41,579
(drove to the sea after hearing the terminally ill patient's wish.)

10
00:00:42,950 --> 00:00:44,879
(After he retired in 2007, he founded...)

11
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:46,249
(Ambulance Wish Foundation...)

12
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:47,719
(and granted the last wish of many patients.)

13
00:01:35,930 --> 00:01:40,840
(If You Wish Upon Me)

14
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:44,639
(Episode 1)

15
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:46,180
(Prison)

16
00:02:09,870 --> 00:02:11,740
(Prison)

17
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:19,280
- Hi. - What's your deal?

18
00:02:31,719 --> 00:02:34,060
Did I do something wrong?

19
00:02:53,909 --> 00:02:54,979
Yoon Gyeo Rye.

20
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:00,080
Hey, Yoon Gyeo Rye!

21
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:04,620
That punk.

22
00:03:10,759 --> 00:03:11,800
(Establish law and order)

23
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:26,479
Who are you? Why did you run away?

24
00:03:27,110 --> 00:03:28,150
That hurts.

25
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:30,750
- Where's Yoon Gyeo Rye? - Let me go.

26
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:33,019
I don't know who that is.

27
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:35,788
I ran away because you suddenly came after me and intimidated me.

28
00:03:35,789 --> 00:03:37,059
Tell me the truth.

29
00:03:37,060 --> 00:03:39,519
He wore this jacket when he went to prison.

30
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:42,188
I found it in the prison trash can.

31
00:03:42,189 --> 00:03:44,529
No! Don't kill me!

32
00:03:44,530 --> 00:03:45,860
I'm sorry. Don't kill me!

33
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,598
I'm sorry. Please don't kill me. I'm begging you.

34
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:52,469
It's all my fault. Please!

35
00:03:56,539 --> 00:03:58,439
I'm sorry.

36
00:03:59,409 --> 00:04:01,610
I'll be better. I'm sorry.

37
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:03,549
I'm sorry.

38
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:06,119
Don't kill me.

39
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,389
I'm sorry.

40
00:04:07,689 --> 00:04:10,319
I'm sorry. Spare my life.

41
00:04:16,689 --> 00:04:18,399
(Seok Jun)

42
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,628
Seok Jun. Long time no see.

43
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:25,039
You want to die? Do you have two lives?

44
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:27,639
I'd appreciate it if you kill me without getting my hands dirty,

45
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:29,970
but if I have two lives, do I have to die twice?

46
00:04:30,139 --> 00:04:32,179
I'd kill you right away as soon as I see you,

47
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:33,779
so I'll ask you one last time.

48
00:04:33,910 --> 00:04:35,508
Where did you siphon off the 320,000 dollars?

49
00:04:35,509 --> 00:04:38,278
Park Hyo Soon said he's never met you or got money from you.

50
00:04:38,279 --> 00:04:40,350
This is crazy.

51
00:04:40,990 --> 00:04:42,050
Look.

52
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:46,560
I met him and gave him the money.

53
00:04:47,089 --> 00:04:48,689
So, Seok Jun.

54
00:04:49,689 --> 00:04:52,159
Stop calling me, you lunatic.

55
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,899
You piece of trash. Are you out of your mind?

56
00:04:58,639 --> 00:04:59,670
Darn.

57
00:05:16,189 --> 00:05:17,659
- Bye. - Thank you.

58
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:19,660
Bye, Somi. Take care.

59
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:39,180
So...

60
00:05:40,709 --> 00:05:41,949
you're saying...

61
00:05:42,850 --> 00:05:44,879
he's...

62
00:05:48,019 --> 00:05:49,149
terminally ill?

63
00:05:49,790 --> 00:05:51,560
Yes, he doesn't have much time left.

64
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:54,089
Surgery won't help.

65
00:05:55,259 --> 00:05:58,229
This is crazy.

66
00:05:58,230 --> 00:05:59,958
You never called me after you left the orphanage,

67
00:05:59,959 --> 00:06:02,170
then you suddenly showed up and asked me to look after the dog.

68
00:06:02,569 --> 00:06:03,769
Of course it's crazy.

69
00:06:04,899 --> 00:06:06,268
Where's the bag?

70
00:06:06,269 --> 00:06:07,339
Wait here.

71
00:06:16,879 --> 00:06:18,120
It's darn heavy.

72
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,759
Is it dangerous?

73
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:31,560
It belongs to me. I only got my stuff back.

74
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:35,970
Hey. Here.

75
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:38,870
Take it.

76
00:06:38,871 --> 00:06:42,170
I don't need this much. It doesn't cost much to stay.

77
00:06:42,670 --> 00:06:45,609
You kept it for me. You didn't take off with it.

78
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:48,179
Take that as compensation for that.

79
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,878
Just take what you can get.

80
00:06:49,879 --> 00:06:51,420
I'd never refuse it.

81
00:06:55,990 --> 00:06:57,990
- Hey. I don't need it. - What?

82
00:06:58,660 --> 00:07:00,489
- For real? - No thanks. Take it back.

83
00:07:00,490 --> 00:07:01,629
Don't regret it.

84
00:07:01,790 --> 00:07:04,529
He won't last long anyway.

85
00:07:05,529 --> 00:07:07,869
Sometimes he'll be in pain and have a seizure.

86
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:09,869
Don't dwell on it too much and you better put him to sleep.

87
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:12,540
Seriously. I'll take care of it.

88
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:15,509
Were we this close?

89
00:07:15,639 --> 00:07:18,339
I'm talking to you as a vet, not as your family from the orphanage.

90
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:22,610
Don't be ridiculous. We're not family.

91
00:07:23,579 --> 00:07:26,378
Let's be honest. You were there only for a short time...

92
00:07:26,379 --> 00:07:28,388
while your rich parents were getting a divorce,

93
00:07:28,389 --> 00:07:31,160
but I walked in there myself to survive. There's a difference.

94
00:07:31,889 --> 00:07:32,959
Bye.

95
00:07:34,759 --> 00:07:36,059
Let's go, baby.

96
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:39,430
Besides, I'm two years older than you. Have you forgotten?

97
00:07:39,629 --> 00:07:42,399
Yoon Gyeo Rye. Hey. What about Jun Kyung?

98
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,540
How's she doing?

99
00:07:45,899 --> 00:07:47,470
You were always together.

100
00:07:53,379 --> 00:07:57,149
Son. Have you seen this before?

101
00:07:57,579 --> 00:07:58,720
No, right?

102
00:07:59,019 --> 00:08:00,589
You've got to see this.

103
00:08:00,889 --> 00:08:02,620
- Sir? - Yes?

104
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,490
What brings you to our hotel?

105
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:06,860
I'm staying here tonight.

106
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:09,290
You're staying in our hotel?

107
00:08:09,829 --> 00:08:10,959
Yes. Is there something wrong?

108
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:15,170
I got money. I can afford it.

109
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:18,170
Hang on.

110
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:28,079
Give me the best room here.

111
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,419
Is that not enough?

112
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:35,889
Here. The most expensive room.

113
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:37,590
Great.

114
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,730
Is this the most expensive room?

115
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,129
- How many rooms are in here? - Sir. It's on your right.

116
00:08:47,929 --> 00:08:48,970
I see.

117
00:08:49,799 --> 00:08:51,240
Gosh.

118
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:54,809
Look at this.

119
00:08:57,409 --> 00:08:58,509
Great.

120
00:09:02,179 --> 00:09:03,480
Amazing.

121
00:09:03,649 --> 00:09:05,449
Check this out.

122
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:07,620
This is huge.

123
00:09:08,820 --> 00:09:10,960
This is awesome.

124
00:09:13,690 --> 00:09:14,690
Awesome.

125
00:09:16,429 --> 00:09:18,029
I can see everything.

126
00:09:19,799 --> 00:09:22,029
Oh, look at that.

127
00:09:22,169 --> 00:09:24,500
Sir. Enjoy your stay.

128
00:09:24,570 --> 00:09:25,600
Thank you.

129
00:09:27,070 --> 00:09:29,710
It's so high.

130
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:33,480
Money is great.

131
00:09:35,879 --> 00:09:37,049
Right.

132
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:40,850
Here.

133
00:09:41,419 --> 00:09:44,960
- It's okay. - You worked hard.

134
00:09:48,659 --> 00:09:50,259
Here. Take it.

135
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,860
- Have a good night. - Thank you.

136
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,539
Bye.

137
00:09:58,269 --> 00:09:59,799
Good night!

138
00:09:59,899 --> 00:10:02,340
Yes. It's crazy!

139
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:07,350
Happy birthday to you

140
00:10:07,710 --> 00:10:10,850
Happy birthday to you

141
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:12,519
Dear...

142
00:10:15,049 --> 00:10:18,889
Dear Yoon Gyeo Rye

143
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:23,230
Happy birthday to you

144
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:46,679
That was a lie!

145
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:54,759
How am I supposed to know when I was born?

146
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:57,230
No one ever told me.

147
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:07,769
Hey. When's your birthday? You don't know?

148
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:16,610
Come on. Eat.

149
00:11:17,919 --> 00:11:19,219
Eat.

150
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,620
Why aren't you eating? You're sick.

151
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:27,489
You think your previous owners who abandoned you...

152
00:11:27,490 --> 00:11:29,460
felt too guilty to eat?

153
00:11:29,590 --> 00:11:32,559
Nonsense. Don't be ridiculous.

154
00:11:33,129 --> 00:11:36,398
If they could feel guilty,

155
00:11:36,399 --> 00:11:38,369
they would've never abandoned you in the first place!

156
00:11:38,370 --> 00:11:41,139
Come on! Eat. You need to eat to survive!

157
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,409
Come on.

158
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:57,049
It's a darn big room.

159
00:12:38,159 --> 00:12:41,269
How beautiful.

160
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:45,200
This is why I can't leave this place.

161
00:12:54,679 --> 00:13:00,320
(Woori Hospice Hospital)

162
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:04,619
- Hello. - Hello.

163
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:06,120
(For donation)

164
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:09,129
Put it away after use.

165
00:13:12,299 --> 00:13:14,230
Oh, hello.

166
00:13:15,899 --> 00:13:17,669
- Hello. - Hello.

167
00:13:18,299 --> 00:13:19,970
Hello.

168
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:23,268
No one picked this up?

169
00:13:23,269 --> 00:13:25,679
How can they just leave? Catch.

170
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:29,309
Have a good day.

171
00:13:45,659 --> 00:13:46,730
Hello.

172
00:13:47,830 --> 00:13:49,699
- Good morning. - Morning.

173
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,939
Hello.

174
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:51,940
(Ward, Cafeteria)

175
00:13:52,899 --> 00:13:54,970
Is it causing trouble again?

176
00:13:55,309 --> 00:13:56,809
- Is it not working? - No.

177
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,610
- There. - Thank you.

178
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,888
Thank you, doctor.

179
00:14:07,889 --> 00:14:09,850
I'm not a doctor.

180
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:11,220
It's hot in here.

181
00:14:11,759 --> 00:14:12,860
Hello.

182
00:14:14,690 --> 00:14:16,428
He's Mr. Kang.

183
00:14:16,429 --> 00:14:18,158
He's a volunteer.

184
00:14:18,159 --> 00:14:19,559
I see.

185
00:14:20,230 --> 00:14:21,970
Thank you for your help.

186
00:14:26,899 --> 00:14:29,609
Ma'am. Good morning.

187
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:31,579
I'm cleaning.

188
00:14:31,580 --> 00:14:33,178
Use the restroom on a different floor.

189
00:14:33,179 --> 00:14:34,749
I have to finish it fast and get to the third floor.

190
00:14:34,750 --> 00:14:38,518
You think I'd pee in front of you?

191
00:14:38,519 --> 00:14:40,820
Did you miss me that much?

192
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:43,819
You don't hesitate to walk in when I'm cleaning.

193
00:14:43,820 --> 00:14:45,220
Don't fall for me.

194
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:48,158
I've never had a boyfriend before,

195
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:50,860
but I only like handsome.

196
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,699
When I was young...

197
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:54,899
Ma'am?

198
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:28,199
I told you to get up on time for breakfast,

199
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,899
but you always sleep in.

200
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:32,269
Okay.

201
00:15:33,070 --> 00:15:36,840
Oh, it's good. It's amazing.

202
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:40,210
Your cooking skill should be awarded.

203
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,909
Especially this coastal hog fennel.

204
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:45,048
- That's right beside. - What?

205
00:15:45,049 --> 00:15:47,580
- It's brachycarpa. - Right. brachycarpa.

206
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:51,559
When I was young, I hated greens.

207
00:15:51,860 --> 00:15:53,719
Now that I'm getting old,

208
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:55,889
I crave greens in the middle of the night.

209
00:15:56,059 --> 00:15:59,158
I'll make it for you as much as you want. Just get up early.

210
00:15:59,159 --> 00:16:02,470
How can someone living in the hospital get here after us?

211
00:16:02,730 --> 00:16:06,700
Nothing upsets me more than preparing a meal twice.

212
00:16:07,039 --> 00:16:08,269
Okay.

213
00:16:12,409 --> 00:16:15,679
You're going with Mr. Yoon today. Are you going to be okay?

214
00:16:17,950 --> 00:16:18,980
Oh, right.

215
00:16:19,279 --> 00:16:22,820
I was going to give him a bath before we hit the road.

216
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:25,120
It must break your heart.

217
00:16:26,059 --> 00:16:28,090
You treated him like your brother.

218
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:36,970
By the way, I thought Nurse Seo was coming for a meal.

219
00:16:37,299 --> 00:16:39,600
Where did she go? I haven't seen her.

220
00:16:40,370 --> 00:16:43,168
She's probably working on the same thing...

221
00:16:43,169 --> 00:16:45,379
in the same place upstairs.

222
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:22,250
Hi.

223
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,480
So when are you becoming an MMA fighter?

224
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:29,150
I don't have time for it.

225
00:17:29,849 --> 00:17:30,849
I'm too busy.

226
00:17:31,289 --> 00:17:32,359
Go.

227
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:41,000
- It's time. - Right.

228
00:17:41,269 --> 00:17:42,470
What about school?

229
00:17:42,829 --> 00:17:45,299
I'll go later. This is more important.

230
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:49,269
Hey.

231
00:17:54,950 --> 00:17:57,849
Mr. Yoon. Is it nice?

232
00:18:09,029 --> 00:18:11,930
My goodness.

233
00:18:12,930 --> 00:18:13,960
Mr. Yoon.

234
00:18:14,829 --> 00:18:17,869
You always wanted to see the snow.

235
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:21,569
It's your wish come true.

236
00:18:25,140 --> 00:18:29,509
In this hospice hospital, we have special people.

237
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:33,049
People who make snow in the middle of summer.

238
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:36,089
Regardless of age, gender, and occupation,

239
00:18:36,589 --> 00:18:38,720
they have beautiful hearts.

240
00:18:39,359 --> 00:18:42,029
We call people who grant the last wish...

241
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:44,930
Team Genie.

242
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:49,700
Today, we're granting Mr. Yoon's last wish...

243
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:53,670
who created Team Genie.

244
00:18:55,369 --> 00:18:56,440
Maybe...

245
00:18:57,509 --> 00:18:59,680
it could be all our wishes.

246
00:19:01,849 --> 00:19:04,849
For the miracle Team Genie has created...

247
00:19:05,980 --> 00:19:08,349
and more to come,

248
00:19:09,390 --> 00:19:11,690
we're praying again.

249
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:19,730
Now you should plan...

250
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:22,730
the Christmas party with your wife...

251
00:19:25,670 --> 00:19:28,109
on the beach in your hometown.

252
00:19:30,609 --> 00:19:31,680
Okay?

253
00:19:33,609 --> 00:19:34,650
Yes.

254
00:19:49,289 --> 00:19:50,289
Gosh.

255
00:19:54,829 --> 00:19:57,700
Life is crazy.

256
00:20:00,470 --> 00:20:01,869
For both you and me...

257
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:07,710
(Come to Goseong!)

258
00:20:11,319 --> 00:20:13,650
Why, do you want to see the ocean?

259
00:20:23,529 --> 00:20:25,759
Shall we go see the ocean for the last time before you die?

260
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:34,369
Let's do that. We have no place to go anyway.

261
00:20:39,839 --> 00:20:43,750
You have what looks like a burn on your skin.

262
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:46,680
It's the skin condition...

263
00:20:47,319 --> 00:20:50,349
from radiotherapy you received.

264
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,518
It's due to weak immune system.

265
00:20:52,519 --> 00:20:55,259
If you apply this ointment, you'll get better soon.

266
00:20:56,230 --> 00:20:58,029
I know it hurts.

267
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:00,730
I'll be quick.

268
00:21:03,099 --> 00:21:04,169
Oh, dear.

269
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:06,000
(Nurses' Lounge)

270
00:21:08,109 --> 00:21:09,839
Where do I start?

271
00:21:10,839 --> 00:21:12,880
- Unit 203. - Okay.

272
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:16,180
Dr. Yang.

273
00:21:17,980 --> 00:21:21,549
Later, you're coming with me, right?

274
00:21:22,019 --> 00:21:24,048
Yes. I promised, after all.

275
00:21:24,049 --> 00:21:25,959
Thank you so much.

276
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:27,390
I was worried about...

277
00:21:28,029 --> 00:21:29,059
Oh, gosh.

278
