He was on his deathbed, but you didn't even call us!

545
00:42:34,659 --> 00:42:37,030
We did.

546
00:42:38,760 --> 00:42:39,928
We left text messages...

547
00:42:39,929 --> 00:42:42,828
and called numerous times, but you never answered.

548
00:42:42,829 --> 00:42:44,469
You should've called until we picked up.

549
00:42:45,530 --> 00:42:47,500
You didn't answer once for three months.

550
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,639
You never once picked up.

551
00:42:55,539 --> 00:42:58,679
But you answered when we called to tell you that he passed away.

552
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:01,719
- Why? For the insurance money? - My gosh.

553
00:43:02,579 --> 00:43:03,750
Who is he?

554
00:43:04,190 --> 00:43:06,018
He leads the volunteer team at the hospital.

555
00:43:06,019 --> 00:43:08,190
He was closest to your father.

556
00:43:10,159 --> 00:43:11,230
Mr. Yoon.

557
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:14,730
I'm here.

558
00:43:29,380 --> 00:43:30,480
You people.

559
00:43:31,510 --> 00:43:34,849
No matter the circumstances,

560
00:43:36,219 --> 00:43:38,420
you should never be shameless, you fools.

561
00:43:39,119 --> 00:43:41,519
Who were the ones that were by his side until his final moments?

562
00:43:42,219 --> 00:43:44,360
That's rich coming from you. Have some shame.

563
00:43:44,559 --> 00:43:47,929
That watch. Hey, isn't it Dad's?

564
00:43:48,699 --> 00:43:51,899
My gosh. I understand that he's dead now,

565
00:43:51,900 --> 00:43:53,968
but how dare you take his watch?

566
00:43:53,969 --> 00:43:55,299
And all things aside, how could you...

567
00:43:55,300 --> 00:43:58,210
let him leave the hospice when he was barely breathing?

568
00:43:59,070 --> 00:44:02,780
I never liked that hospice hospital to begin with.

569
00:44:03,110 --> 00:44:06,249
You should've treated him until the end. How could you give up?

570
00:44:06,250 --> 00:44:07,920
- Exactly! - People will speak ill of us.

571
00:44:08,150 --> 00:44:10,289
I guess you have to put the blame on us...

572
00:44:11,050 --> 00:44:13,889
to free yourselves from the guilt of being terrible children.

573
00:44:14,219 --> 00:44:16,129
- What? You jerk. Let go. - Hey, what's your problem?

574
00:44:16,130 --> 00:44:18,129
- What's your deal? - Hey, let go.

575
00:44:18,130 --> 00:44:20,400
- Hey! What is your problem? - I can't believe this.

576
00:44:20,829 --> 00:44:21,929
You.

577
00:44:24,730 --> 00:44:26,340
Your father said this to me.

578
00:44:27,869 --> 00:44:29,769
"You can't choose when you're born,"

579
00:44:29,869 --> 00:44:32,239
"so be it."

580
00:44:35,110 --> 00:44:37,610
"But I want to choose when I die."

581
00:44:38,550 --> 00:44:39,780
This watch.

582
00:44:41,219 --> 00:44:43,789
He gave it to me and said his time was now over.

583
00:44:46,460 --> 00:44:47,590
He said...

584
00:44:49,829 --> 00:44:51,389
it was my time from now on.

585
00:44:56,070 --> 00:44:57,429
You pieces of trash.

586
00:45:00,869 --> 00:45:02,598
- What? - Move.

587
00:45:02,599 --> 00:45:04,969
- Hey! - Get back here!

588
00:45:05,340 --> 00:45:07,739
- I can't believe this! - Unbelievable! Hey!

589
00:45:08,039 --> 00:45:09,949
- What the... - What will you do about this?

590
00:45:10,650 --> 00:45:14,279
(Rest In Peace)

591
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:16,988
(Taepyung Industries)

592
00:45:16,989 --> 00:45:19,690
(Sehan Company)

593
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:29,159
His family was right.

594
00:45:30,329 --> 00:45:33,469
We were too idealistic.

595
00:45:35,070 --> 00:45:38,539
I don't think I can help you anymore.

596
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:43,279
- Dr. Yang. - A car accident, violating the law,

597
00:45:43,280 --> 00:45:45,750
in an ambulance driven by a stranger...

598
00:45:47,480 --> 00:45:49,019
On top of that, he even received CPR.

599
00:45:50,420 --> 00:45:51,820
He even signed the advance directive.

600
00:45:54,690 --> 00:45:58,559
That's not what someone should go through in their final moments.

601
00:45:59,260 --> 00:46:00,360
I'm sorry.

602
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:06,840
I know you did your best. I should get going.

603
00:46:16,610 --> 00:46:21,019
(Chapel of Rest)

604
00:46:59,889 --> 00:47:01,289
My goodness.

605
00:47:02,190 --> 00:47:03,590
You're here.

606
00:47:04,190 --> 00:47:07,030
Oh, you look nice today.

607
00:47:07,760 --> 00:47:09,099
I showered yesterday.

608
00:47:10,099 --> 00:47:11,769
Is Mr. Kang not back yet?

609
00:47:12,099 --> 00:47:15,639
No. This is so unlike him.

610
00:47:16,570 --> 00:47:19,239
It's been almost a week already.

611
00:47:19,269 --> 00:47:22,380
I think he's still shocked by Mr. Yoon's death.

612
00:47:28,619 --> 00:47:30,250
Wake up!

613
00:47:30,849 --> 00:47:33,989
The early bird is tired.

614
00:47:43,800 --> 00:47:45,230
- Gosh. - Oh, dear.

615
00:47:46,469 --> 00:47:49,039
What are you doing here?

616
00:47:49,539 --> 00:47:51,170
I thought you were doing well.

617
00:47:55,110 --> 00:47:59,349
I slept like a baby, as if I'm back home after a long time.

618
00:48:01,550 --> 00:48:02,650
My gosh.

619
00:48:02,849 --> 00:48:06,619
Actually, no. This is my home, right?

620
00:48:07,059 --> 00:48:10,590
Hey, don't say stuff like that.

621
00:48:10,630 --> 00:48:12,488
That place is your home now.

622
00:48:12,489 --> 00:48:15,759
And it's about time you turned over a new leaf.

623
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:16,900
This place is...

624
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:22,199
Stop coming here!

625
00:48:23,170 --> 00:48:25,210
You said many people needed you there.

626
00:48:26,170 --> 00:48:27,739
They call you "Captain" and stuff.

627
00:48:27,780 --> 00:48:30,309
Oh, right. That's true.

628
00:48:30,650 --> 00:48:33,449
They're such a nuisance.

629
00:48:35,579 --> 00:48:39,250
Goodness. They must be looking for me now.

630
00:48:40,159 --> 00:48:41,360
I should get going.

631
00:48:43,030 --> 00:48:44,130
That punk...

632
00:48:45,260 --> 00:48:47,329
Does he not visit you these days?

633
00:48:49,199 --> 00:48:51,030
I haven't seen him in a while.

634
00:48:54,239 --> 00:48:57,670
That's a relief, unlike everything else you said.

635
00:49:03,809 --> 00:49:06,719
Well, I should get going now.

636
00:49:07,619 --> 00:49:11,750
And seriously, stop drinking already. What is this?

637
00:49:13,190 --> 00:49:15,289
Are you beggars or what?

638
00:49:17,130 --> 00:49:18,190
I'm off.

639
00:49:19,260 --> 00:49:21,299
Okay. Get back safely.

640
00:49:21,300 --> 00:49:22,300
All right.

641
00:49:22,630 --> 00:49:25,500
How did he hurt his leg?

642
00:49:25,730 --> 00:49:29,539
Why worry about a former homeless man when you're still homeless?

643
00:49:29,739 --> 00:49:31,710
Just worry about earning enough money to buy soju.

644
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:32,840
Come on.

645
00:49:33,480 --> 00:49:35,940
(Volunteers' Lounge)

646
00:49:36,650 --> 00:49:39,650
What are we going to do now that Mr. Kang is hurt?

647
00:49:40,119 --> 00:49:43,219
Who will drive the ambulance?

648
00:49:45,219 --> 00:49:47,658
We'll find someone. He's not the only one who can drive.

649
00:49:47,659 --> 00:49:49,929
That happened because no one else could drive.

650
00:49:50,090 --> 00:49:51,689
You haven't driven in years,

651
00:49:51,690 --> 00:49:53,459
and Dr. Yang is a novice driver,

652
00:49:53,460 --> 00:49:55,429
so he can't drive an ambulance.

653
00:49:55,559 --> 00:49:56,670
That's right.

654
00:49:57,070 --> 00:50:00,669
Mr. Hwang cancelled his driver's license last year.

655
00:50:00,670 --> 00:50:02,899
You ladies and I can't drive at all.

656
00:50:02,900 --> 00:50:04,939
Then can't we just hire someone?

657
00:50:04,940 --> 00:50:07,439
- Yes. - We can't afford that.

658
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:10,380
Oh, right! You know, in the fourth floor safe,

659
00:50:10,610 --> 00:50:11,879
there is a lot of strong morphine.

660
00:50:11,880 --> 00:50:14,049
If we sneak out a handful and sell them,

661
00:50:14,050 --> 00:50:15,379
we can easily hire someone,

662
00:50:15,380 --> 00:50:18,649
and we'll have enough money to feed two generations...

663
00:50:18,650 --> 00:50:19,889
Seo Jin.

664
00:50:21,260 --> 00:50:24,360
Have you ever gotten your teeth knocked out while eating corn?

665
00:50:25,030 --> 00:50:28,030
If you know me well enough, you can't say stuff like that.

666
00:50:30,400 --> 00:50:31,768
Oh, right.

667
00:50:31,769 --> 00:50:34,968
This is Chodang corn. No wonder it's so delicious.

668
00:50:34,969 --> 00:50:36,969
I'm not making this sound with my mouth right now.

669
00:50:40,039 --> 00:50:42,308
- I'm back. - Mr. Kang!

670
00:50:42,309 --> 00:50:45,149
My gosh. Where have you been? You didn't even call us once.

671
00:50:45,150 --> 00:50:46,209
We were worried.

672
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:48,380
Right, is your leg okay?

673
00:50:48,750 --> 00:50:49,789
Yes.

674
00:50:50,449 --> 00:50:52,948
I'll have to keep the cast on for the time being.

675
00:50:52,949 --> 00:50:55,960
See? My goodness.

676
00:50:56,530 --> 00:50:58,889
Where are we going to find someone who can drive?

677
00:51:04,500 --> 00:51:07,239
Case Number 2021-GY0819.

678
00:51:07,300 --> 00:51:10,570
Violation of the Road Traffic Act.

679
00:51:10,969 --> 00:51:13,479
Causing an accident that injured three people including Mr. Kang.

680
00:51:13,480 --> 00:51:17,749
Ergo, Mr. Yoon Gyeo Rye shall be fined 5,000 dollars.

681
00:51:17,750 --> 00:51:19,079
Look, Mr. Attorney.

682
00:51:19,679 --> 00:51:22,650
This is not fair. It's not like I did it on purpose.

683
00:51:23,150 --> 00:51:25,288
This is too much.

684
00:51:25,289 --> 00:51:26,420
Please.

685
00:51:27,489 --> 00:51:29,219
Do you want to go back to jail for contempt of court?

686
00:51:30,329 --> 00:51:31,428
Darn it.

687
00:51:31,429 --> 00:51:32,760
(Judge)

688
00:51:33,199 --> 00:51:35,760
If Mr. Yoon is not financially able to pay the fine,

689
00:51:36,159 --> 00:51:37,829
he may work off the fine with community service.

690
00:51:40,199 --> 00:51:41,599
Hey, Mr. Attorney.

691
00:51:42,139 --> 00:51:44,968
Let's make sure we're on the same page. I admit everything,

692
00:51:44,969 --> 00:51:48,840
but I cannot pay the fine.

693
00:51:49,010 --> 00:51:50,550
I have a lot of money!

694
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:52,479
Seriously, I'm loaded.

695
00:51:52,480 --> 00:51:55,219
I swear, I can afford to pay it. But the thing is...

696
00:51:55,980 --> 00:51:57,619
I refuse to give money to the government.

697
00:51:58,389 --> 00:52:02,059
Why should I pay a fine when the government has done nothing for me?

698
00:52:02,289 --> 00:52:04,130
Hey, mister. I refuse to pay the fine!

699
00:52:19,940 --> 00:52:22,039
His name is Yoon Gyeo Rye. He's my friend.

700
00:52:22,139 --> 00:52:24,578
We were supposed to meet up here today, but he's not picking up.

701
00:52:24,579 --> 00:52:25,710
Hello.

702
00:52:34,889 --> 00:52:38,530
Darn it, Sonny...

703
00:52:39,590 --> 00:52:40,730
Gosh.

704
00:52:46,199 --> 00:52:47,469
Hello, sir.

705
00:53:15,659 --> 00:53:18,268
Hey, Sonny. What's wrong?

706
00:53:18,269 --> 00:53:19,699
Are you okay? Are you not feeling well?

707
00:53:20,969 --> 00:53:22,900
Gosh, what is the matter with you? This is nuts.

708
00:53:36,989 --> 00:53:38,289
Doors are closing.

709
00:53:38,750 --> 00:53:40,760
Hey, let's go this way.

710
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:57,440
Go all the way to the end.

711
00:54:07,079 --> 00:54:08,079
Hello.

712
00:54:12,690 --> 00:54:13,690
Shoot.

713
00:54:15,590 --> 00:54:16,690
Darn it!

714
00:54:36,539 --> 00:54:38,780
Hey, Jin Gu!

715
00:54:39,679 --> 00:54:40,849
(Animal Hospital)

716
00:54:41,250 --> 00:54:43,079
I brought Sonny.

717
00:54:52,030 --> 00:54:53,059
Here.

718
00:55:04,139 --> 00:55:05,369
Isn't he heavy?

719
00:55:06,739 --> 00:55:08,340
He's as light as a feather.

720
00:55:09,039 --> 00:55:10,909
It looks like he's been through a lot.

721
00:55:11,550 --> 00:55:13,250
I suggest you just let him go.

722
00:55:14,880 --> 00:55:15,949
Okay?

723
00:55:17,219 --> 00:55:18,819
It's a sin to keep him alive...

724
00:55:18,820 --> 00:55:21,789
knowing how much pain he is in just to fulfill your greed.

725
00:55:26,929 --> 00:55:28,199
He must be in a lot of pain now.

726
00:55:30,300 --> 00:55:31,429
Gosh...

727
00:55:46,349 --> 00:55:47,619
Darn it.

728
00:55:54,559 --> 00:55:56,860
Okay, yes.

729
00:55:59,630 --> 00:56:00,699
So you've made up your mind, right?

730
00:56:05,829 --> 00:56:07,039
Okay, you made the right decision.

731
00:56:12,340 --> 00:56:14,380
Sonny, let's go.

732
00:56:16,280 --> 00:56:17,349
Come here.

733
00:56:18,949 --> 00:56:20,380
Come here. Good boy.

734
00:56:21,079 --> 00:56:22,119
Oh, no.

735
00:56:28,289 --> 00:56:29,360
What is it?

736
00:56:31,530 --> 00:56:34,429
Hey, you have to go now.

737
00:56:42,940 --> 00:56:44,340
Why? Do you want to live a little longer?

738
00:56:45,940 --> 00:56:48,210
You weren't like this at the beach. Do you not like the hospital?

739
00:56:53,409 --> 00:56:56,179
Hey, not today.

740
00:56:56,579 --> 00:56:57,819
Hey, he must be in a lot of pain now...

741
00:56:57,820 --> 00:56:59,949
Hey! What do you even know?

742
00:57:00,320 --> 00:57:01,459
You have no idea.

743
00:57:01,460 --> 00:57:03,630
Maybe he wants to live a few more days.

744
00:57:04,329 --> 00:57:05,329
I mean...

745
00:57:06,260 --> 00:57:09,300
He might want to live a bit longer even if he's in a lot of pain.

746
00:57:10,429 --> 00:57:13,399
And who knows? There could be things he wants to do before he dies.

747
00:57:13,400 --> 00:57:14,469
I'm off.

748
00:57:38,530 --> 00:57:39,928
(Western District Court)

749
00:57:39,929 --> 00:57:41,429
(Notice of Fine)

750
00:57:43,670 --> 00:57:47,940
Darn, seriously...

751
00:57:52,909 --> 00:57:54,279
(You may complete community service at Woori Hospice Hospital...)

752
00:57:54,280 --> 00:57:55,510
(in lieu of paying the fine.)

753
00:57:56,039 --> 00:57:57,210
What is "hospice"?

754
00:58:04,820 --> 00:58:06,119
(Hospice)

755
00:58:07,789 --> 00:58:09,859
(A type of health care that focuses on the palliation...)

756
00:58:09,860 --> 00:58:11,459
(of terminally ill patients and attending...)

757
00:58:11,460 --> 00:58:13,230
(to their emotional needs at the end of life.)

758
00:58:27,110 --> 00:58:28,639
It's a sin to keep him alive...

759
00:58:29,079 --> 00:58:32,009
knowing how much pain he is in just to fulfill your greed.

760
00:58:32,010 --> 00:58:33,280
He must be in a lot of pain now.

761
00:58:35,750 --> 00:58:37,319
(Hospice care focuses on the quality of life...)

762
00:58:37,320 --> 00:58:38,750
(for the terminally ill and their caregivers.)

763
00:58:49,929 --> 00:58:51,300
Mr. Kang!

764
00:58:51,929 --> 00:58:53,469
Someone will be here to do community service.

765
00:58:54,170 --> 00:58:55,900
Oh, really?

766
00:58:56,699 --> 00:58:58,039
It must've been decided then.

767
00:58:58,840 --> 00:59:01,179
You knew about it?

768
00:59:03,139 --> 00:59:04,250
Well...

769
00:59:06,079 --> 00:59:08,849
- Oh, sir. - Yes?

770
00:59:10,550 --> 00:59:11,550
Hello.

771
00:59:13,889 --> 00:59:15,690
I requested it.

772
00:59:15,889 --> 00:59:18,429
I see. That's great.

773
00:59:19,059 --> 00:59:20,659
This person must be a good driver, right?

774
00:59:21,130 --> 00:59:23,428
Well, I guess that would depend...

775
00:59:23,429 --> 00:59:25,299
on how you define "good".

776
00:59:25,300 --> 00:59:26,329
We'll wait and see...

777
00:59:28,800 --> 00:59:30,000
I'm sure he'll be fine.

778
00:59:38,510 --> 00:59:41,679
If the pain becomes unbearable, please let us know.

779
00:59:41,849 --> 00:59:43,219
We'll give you an analgesic injection.

780
00:59:47,460 --> 00:59:49,559
Oh, right. Sir.

781
00:59:50,119 --> 00:59:52,259
Your wife is buying you a cool new outfit with her chit fund.

782
00:59:52,260 --> 00:59:53,960
She'll be here later today.

783
00:59:55,300 --> 00:59:56,360
Just wait a couple of hours.

784
00:59:57,130 --> 00:59:59,130
Someone is coming here today to do community service.

785
00:59:59,369 --> 01:00:01,599
- Really? - Oh, that's great.

786
01:00:02,170 --> 01:00:03,808
I wonder if it's a guy.

787
01:00:03,809 --> 01:00:05,768
You heard him say it was for community service.

788
01:00:05,769 --> 01:00:06,980
She may be desperate, but...

789
01:00:07,579 --> 01:00:08,639
Me?

790
01:00:09,809 --> 01:00:12,649
Come on. I'm not that desperate.

791
01:00:12,650 --> 01:00:14,650
That's right. There's Dr. Yang.

792
01:00:15,349 --> 01:00:18,149
I think Dr. Yang has a crush on you.

793
01:00:18,150 --> 01:00:19,819
- What? Really? - Yes.

794
01:00:19,820 --> 01:00:21,920
My gosh! That's so great!

795
01:00:22,960 --> 01:00:26,788
- He comes from a family of doctors. - Is that right?

796
01:00:26,789 --> 01:00:29,159
He's an elite doctor who is a gentleman.

797
01:00:32,869 --> 01:00:35,070
My gosh, you couldn't be more wrong.

798
01:00:35,469 --> 01:00:37,969
You really can't read the room, can you?

799
01:00:38,610 --> 01:00:41,638
Dr. Yang can't stand me.

800
01:00:41,639 --> 01:00:44,210
He thinks I'm a troublemaker who always does useless things.

801
01:00:45,610 --> 01:00:47,779
Dr. Yang has a crush on me? Oh, please.

802
01:00:47,780 --> 01:00:48,949
That was hilarious.

803
01:00:51,090 --> 01:00:53,590
Oh, dear. She sure can't take hints.

804
01:00:54,860 --> 01:00:56,090
She's a nice girl though.

805
01:01:01,530 --> 01:01:03,630
(Cathedral, Annex, Retreat House)

806
01:01:12,670 --> 01:01:14,210
This punk...

807
01:01:28,489 --> 01:01:29,558
He's not here yet, right?

808
01:01:29,559 --> 01:01:31,988
Sunny. Why are you here already? What about school?

809
01:01:31,989 --> 01:01:33,260
I left early today.

810
